8. A method, comprising:
identifying a Transparent Interconnection of Lots of Links (TRILL) routing bridge (RBridge) identifier in a first packet;
identifying a Fibre Channel (FC) domain identifier in a second packet;
indicating a virtual switch identifier associated with a switch as a source address for the first or second packet; and
initiating a Fibre Channel over IP (FCIP) tunnel operable to encapsulate the first and second packets.

15. A computing system, comprising:
a processor;
a non-transitory computer-readable storage medium storing instructions which when executed by the processor causes the processor to perform a method, the method comprising;
identifying a Transparent Interconnection of Lots of Links (TRILL) routing bridge (RBridge) identifier in a first packet;
identifying a Fibre Channel (FC) domain identifier in a second packet
indicating a virtual switch identifier associated with a switch as a source address for the first or second packet; and
initiating a Fibre Channel over IP (FCIP) tunnel operable to encapsulate the first and second packets.
